#note This pre-endgame is a really close call between blocking row 14 or not. Right now, I'm vulnerable to row 14 Z bingos (notably SIEROZEM, which is available without the blank). However, if I sacrifice too many points to block (for instance, by playing DEMIT at 14G), I was concerned about being outrun by a Z play on column N  (he could have ZOMbIE, ZONuLE or ZyMOSE). I estimate the odds of him having a big Z play at 6-7%, versus odds of a big Z bingo at 3% (I calculated these percentages after the game, not during). However, when he plays big Z plays he only wins about half the time (estimated by playing through subsequent pre-endgames), so I evaluate MIDST and DEMIT as roughly even. Make sense? :P
